caption.center: DANIEL GONZALEZ CASTANEDA, Appellant v. THE STATE OF TEXAS.

court.center: Court of Criminal Appeals of Texas.

posture.unpublished: [EDITOR'S NOTE: This case is unpublished as indicated by the issuing court.] On Appellant's Petition for Discretionary Review from the Thirteenth Court of Appeals Hidalgo County.

opinion_text.unpublished:
The petition for discretionary review violates Rule of Appellate Procedure 68.4(i), because the petition does not contain a copy of the opinion of the court of appeals.
The petition is struck. See Rule of Appellate Procedure 68.6.
The petitioner may redraw the petition. The redrawn petition and copies must be filed in the COURT OF CRIMINAL APPEALS within thirty days after the date of this order.
